set()-->internal flag value will become true and it represents GREEN signal for all waiting threads
 
clear()-->internal flag will become fALse and it represents RED signal for all waiting threads

isSet()-->this method can be used whether the event is set or not 

Wait()-->thread will  wait until event is set


condition method
----------------

acquire()-->to acquire condition object before producing or consuming items i.e thread acquiring internal lock 

release()-->to release condition object after  producing or consuming items i.e thread release internal lock 

wait()-->to wait until getting notification or time expired

notify-->to give notification for one  waiting thread
notify all--> to give notification for all waiting threads 
